return {
	["Rod synthesis succesful."] = "Synteza pretu pomyslna.",
	["You don't have any fuel rods."] = "Nie masz przy sobie zadnych pretow.",
	["You dont have any fuel."] = "Nie masz przy sobie paliwa",
	["You refilled the fuel tank."] = "Doladowales zbiornik",
	["Current fuel tank status: "] = "Aktutalny status zbiornika: ",
	["As i said, go to the Karaiby."] = "Tak jak mowilem. Udaj sie na karaiby.",
	["Guten tag. Was hast du zu sagen?"] = "Guten tag. Was hast du zu sagen?",
	["I'll tell you that your German is terrible. I served with Friedrich Knopf, i knew Friedrich Knopf, Friedrich Knopf was a friend of mine. My dear, are not Friedrich Knopf. So what are you looking for here?"] = "Powiem Ci, ze twoj niemiecki jest okropny. Poza tym znalem Friedricha Knopfa, i to w zadnym wypadku nie jestes Pan. Czego tu zatem szukasz?",
	["Tell me immediately what you're looking for!"] = "Natychmiast mow czego tu szukasz!",
	["So you stole the identity of one of my employees to work for me? I hire anyone anyway. Alright, I have a first task for you: the new bartender doesn't know how to make my favorite drink. Find my recipe for 'Booty Sweat Lean' so he knows exactly what ingredients to use. You'll find a chest with recipes on the top floor of the library. Just photocopy the recipe and come back to me."] = "W wiec ukradles tozsamosc mojemu pracownikowi, zeby moc robic u mnie? Ja i tak przyjmuje do pracy kazdego. No dobra, to mam dla Ciebie pierwsze zadanie: nowy barman nie ogarnia jak zrobic moj ulubiony drink. Znajdz moj przepis na soczek z foczek, aby wiedzial jakich dokladnie skladnikow uzyc. Na najwyzszm pietrze biblioteki znajdziesz skrzynie z przepisami. Po prostu zkseruj przepis i wroc do mnie.",
	["Unfortunately, I lost the key to the library. I'm afraid you'll have to find another way to get upstairs and find that {recipe}. Maybe try being a Spider-Man."] = "Niestety, zgubilem klucz do bilbiteki. Obawiam sie, ze bedziesz musial znalezc inny sposob, aby sie dostac na gore i znalezc ten {przepis}. Moze sproboj na spidermana.",
	["Very well done! I have another task for you. You've probably noticed that the castle is overrun by partygoers. They're no eagles, so they don't know how to behave. They recently damaged part of the castle in the east wing. I hired no one other than Boguslaw Lecina to repair it. Now, not only do I have a damaged wall, but there are also grooves from the sanding. Or maybe it's just residue from his cigarettes that settled on the wall? It's not important. Find his toolbox and take one hammer from it. Then go to the waterworks and loosen the valve in the lower part. There's so much mess and I dont even know what else, that we can't flush corpses down the toilet anymore."] = "Bardzo dobra robota! Bede miec dla Ciebie kolejne zadanie. Zauwazyles pewnie, ze w calym domu zalegli sie pato-imprezowicze. Orlami to oni nie sa, wiec nie umieja sie zachowac. Ostatnio zepsuli czesc zamku we wschodnim skrzydle. Do naprawy zatrudnilem nikogo innego jak Boguslawa Lecine. Teraz nie dosc, ze mam rozwalona sciane to jeszce zaglebienia sie porobily od szlifowania. A moze to tylko osad z jego szlugow sie tak ulozyl na scianie? Malo istotne. Znajdz jego pierdolnik i zabierz jeden mlotek z jego beczki z narzedziami. Potem udaj sie do wodociagow i poluzuj zawor w nizszej czesci. Tyle syfu i nie powiem czego, ze nie da sie juz spuszczac zwlok w kiblu.",
	["I have another task for you. You've probably noticed that the castle is overrun by partygoers. They're no eagles, so they don't know how to behave. They recently damaged part of the castle in the east wing. I hired no one other than Boguslaw Lecina to repair it. Now, not only do I have a damaged wall, but there are also grooves from the sanding. Or maybe it's just residue from his cigarettes that settled on the wall? It's not important. Find his toolbox and take one hammer from it. Then go to the waterworks and loosen the valve in the lower part. There's so much mess and I dont even know what else, that we can't flush corpses down the toilet anymore."] = "Bede miec dla Ciebie kolejne zadanie. Zauwazyles pewnie, ze w calym domu zalegli sie pato-imprezowicze. Orlami to oni nie sa, wiec nie umieja sie zachowac. Ostatnio zepsuli czesc zamku we wschodnim skrzydle. Do naprawy zatrudnilem nikogo innego jak Boguslawa Lecine. Teraz nie dosc, ze mam rozwalona sciane to jeszce zaglebienia sie porobily od szlifowania. A moze to tylko osad z jego szlugow sie tak ulozyl na scianie? Malo istotne. Znajdz jego pierdolnik i zabierz jeden mlotek z jego beczki z narzedziami. Potem udaj sie do wodociagow i poluzuj zawor w nizszej czesci. Tyle syfu i nie powiem czego, ze nie da sie juz spuszczac zwlok w kiblu.",
	["Come back when you've obtained the recipe for my favorite drink."] = "Wroc jak juz zdobedziesz przepis na moj ulubiony drinczek.",
	["As I mentioned, Lecina worked in the eastern part of the castle. Take one hammer from his toolbox and use it to loosen the valve in the waterworks."] = "Tak jak mowilem, Lecina pracowal we wschodniej czesci zamku. Wez sobie jeden mlotek z jego beczki i uzyj go do poluzowania zaworu w wodociagach.",
	["You did well. Listen, there's a very old room in the castle's basement, and inside it, there's an even older chest. One of my great-grandfathers left it there. The chest is enchanted, so it can't be opened just like that. I think it will open on its own if you solve the riddle. If you manage to open it, come back to me and report what you found inside."] = "Dobrze sie spisales. Sluchaj, w podziemiach zamku jest bardzo stary pokoj, a w nim jeszcze starsza skrzynia. Zostawil ja tam ktorys z moich pradziadow. Zamek w skrzyni jest zaczarowany, wiec nie mozna jej od tak otworzyc. Mysle, ze sama sie otworzy, jesli rozwiazesz zagadke. Jezeli uda Ci sie ja otworzyc, to wroc do mnie i zrelacjonuj co znalazles w srodku.",
	["My great-grandmother, a witch, once mentioned that to open the chest, I would need some runes. I don't know anything about magic, so I can't help you with that."] = "Moja prababacia, czarownica, wspominala kiedys, ze zeby moc otworzyc te skrzynie, bede potrzebowac jakies runy. Ja sie na magii nie znam, wiec Ci nie pomoge.",
	["So, did you manage to find anything?"] = "I jak? Udalo Ci sie cos znalezc?",
	["Oh, that old man! What's this much of experience points worths in these times... You can keep them."] = "A to stary dziad! Co to jest tyle expa w tych czasach... Mozesz je sobie zachowac.",
	["I have one more thing you can help me with. I heard that people who visit the southern archipelago disappear under mysterious circumstances. Investigate this matter."] = "Mam jeszcze jedna rzecz, z ktora mozesz mi pomoc. Slyszalem, ze ludzie, ktorzy zwiedzaja poludniowy archipelag znikaja w tajemniczych okolicznosciach. Zbadaj te sprawe.",
	["As I said, beachgoers have been disappearing in the southern archipelago. Try looking there."] = "Tak jak mowilem: plazowicze znikali na poludniowym archipelagu. Sproboj tam poszukac.",
	["Thank you for your help. I think I have a suitable reward for you. Perhaps you'll be interested in an ancient artifact I lost somewhere in the northern dump. You can keep it if you find it."] = "Dziekuje za pomoc. Mysle, ze mam dla Ciebie odpowiednia nagrode. Byc moze zainteresuje Cie pewien prawdawny artefakt, ktory zgubilem gdzies na polnocnym wysypisku. Mozesz go sobie zatrzymac, jesli tylko go znajdziesz.",
	["Test test one two. Hello Petrus, can you hear me? What an irony... Alright, to the point: Thanks to the power of my justice and with the help of the King of Rats, Tomek, I managed to gather all the fragments of my soul back together. These fragments traveled through the endless cosmos, but I found them all and merged them. I was trapped in that state for what seemed like ages. During that time, I managed to shed my human shell. Wait... who am I?"] = "Test test raz raz. Halo pjoter, slychac mnie? Co za ironia... No dobra, do rzeczy: Dzieki sile mej sprawiedliwosci i z pomoca krola szczurow udalo mi sie pozbierac z powrotem wszystkie fragmenty mej duszy do kupy. Fragmenty te podrozowaly przez niezmierzony kosmos, ale udalo mi sie je wszystkie odnalezc i ze soba scalic. Bylem uwieziony w tym stanie przez, zdawalo sie, wieki. W tym czasie udalo mi sie zrzucic ludzka powloke. Chwila... kim ja jestem?",
	["Rat of Kings... Yes, I used to be called that. But I'm no longer the Rat of Kings. I am Astral Janus, and I have a {mission} for you!"] = "Szczur Krolow... Tak, tak mnie kiedys nazywano. Juz nie nazywam sie szczur krolow. Jam jest Janusz Gwiezdny i mam dla Ciebie {misje} do wypelnienia!",
	["Our latest target is a notorious businessman known for supporting literal fascists. He's hiding in one of his bases in space. You won't be able to reach him by conventional means, so you can start by going to the Usha'Yaan Forge. They specialize in manufacturing various spacecraft-like products."] = "Naszym najnowszym celem jest notoryczny biznesmen, ktory znany jest ze wspierania literalnych faszystow. Ukrywa sie na jednej ze swoich baz w kosmosie. Z buta sie do niego nie dostaniesz, wiec swoje pierwsze kroki mozesz skierowac do Kuzni Usha'Yaan. Zajmuja sie tam manufaktura roznego rodzaju wyrobow i produktow statkopodobnych.",
	["The Usha'Yaan Forge located in the deepest chasms in the dwarven caves on Hurghada. To gain access to the forge, you need to know a special {codeword} and recite it in ancient dwarven just outside the entrance on the third Sunday of the leap year. Although I'm not entirely sure about the last requirements. Inside, you'll find Qasim the blacksmith, who will tell you how to craft a new spaceship."] = "Kuznia Usha'Yaan znajduje sie gleboko w jaskiniach krasnoludow na hurghadzie. Aby uzyskac dostep do kuzni musisz znac specjalne {haslo} i wypowiedziec je w starozytnej krasnoludzkiej mowie stojac tuz przed wejsciem w trzecia niedziele miesiaca w przestepnym roku. Chociaz co do tych ostatnich wymogow to nie jestem pewnien. W srodku znajdziesz kowala Qasima, ktory powie ci w jaki sposob wyprodukowac nowy statek.",
	["Qasim, also known to many as Cassim, once had a younger brother, who, against his wishes, tried to enter the Usha'Yaan Forge. He didn't know the password when he was near the sealed doors. Suddenly, an opportunity arose - he overheard his brother and a few accomplices heading for the forge. He hid behind nearby rocks, right by the lava lake. Everyone there is accustomed to high temperatures, so the position he found himself in wasn't too uncomfortable. Eventually, he managed to eavesdrop on the password. And the password is... Well, all I know is that his younger brother now was one of the only people who know this password."] = "Qasim, nazywany przez wielu Cassim, mial kiedys mlodszego brata, ktory wbrew jego woli probowal wtargnac do kuzni Usha'Yaan. Nie znal on hasla, gdy byl w okolicy zakletych drzwi. Nagle nadarzyla sie okazja - ulyszal jak jego brat i kilku wspolnikow szlo do kuzni. Schowal sie za pobliskimi skalami, tuz przy jezorze lawy. Wszyscy tam sa przyzwyczajeni do wysokich temperatur, stad pozycja, w ktorej sie znalazl, nie doskwierala mu w sposob znaczny. Ostatecznie udalo mu sie podsluchac haslo. A haslo to... No coz, wiem tylko ze mlodszy brat od tego momentu byl w nielicznym gronie, ktore znalo tajne haslo.",
	["I can't really remember his name.. I think it was something like Al..?"] = "Mam jego imie na koncu jezyka... To chyba bylo cos w stylu Al..",
	["Yes! That what his name exactly."] = "Tak, wlasnie tak sie nazywal.",
	["Good job. Thanks to you, there's more justice in this world. Here's your reward. Now go back to Tomek. He said he has a problem with his old hag."] = "Dobra robota. Dzieki tobie jest na tym swiecie wiecej sprawiedliwosci. Wybierz swoja nagrode: {axe}, {sword}, {mace}, {bow}, {rod}, {wand} (exercise weapon).",
	["Identifiziere dich, Soldat!"] = "Identifiziere dich, Soldat!",
	["Lieutenant, warum ist deine Nase so klein? Dennoch. Haben wir einen Hinrichtungsbefehl auf Rubelstein bestatigt?"] = "Lieutenant, warum ist deine Nase so klein? Dennoch. Haben wir einen Hinrichtungsbefehl auf Rubelstein bestatigt?",
	["Eine kleine Betruger... Wachen, zu den Waffen!"] = "Eine kleine Betruger... Wachen, zu den Waffen!",
	["Wir werden ihn hinrichten lassen. Vielen Dank fur Ihre Zusammenarbeit. Ausserdem habe ich eine {Mission} fur Sie, Leutnant."] = "Wir werden ihn hinrichten lassen. Vielen Dank fur Ihre Zusammenarbeit. Ausserdem habe ich eine {Mission} fur Sie, Leutnant.",
	["Alles in Ordnung, obwohl wir vor einigen Tagen einen Sicherheitsverstoss hatten und den Fluchtigen immer noch nicht finden konnen. Ausserdem habe ich eine {Mission} fur Sie, Leutnant."] = "Alles in Ordnung, obwohl wir vor einigen Tagen einen Sicherheitsverstoss hatten und den Fluchtigen immer noch nicht finden konnen. Ausserdem habe ich eine {Mission} fur Sie, Leutnant.",
	["Ausserdem habe ich eine {Mission} fur Sie, Leutnant."] = "Ausserdem habe ich eine {Mission} fur Sie, Leutnant.",
	["Uberbringe diese Information an Hugo Boss in seiner Zentrale: 'Wir haben einen Bauplan fur eine experimentelle {Uberfabrik} entwickelt'."] = "Uberbringe diese Information an Hugo Boss in seiner Zentrale: 'Wir haben einen Bauplan fur eine experimentelle {Uberfabrik} entwickelt'.",
	["Ich habe den Ort des Hugo Boss-Hauptquartiers an Ihr Schiff geschickt."] = "Ich habe den Ort des Hugo Boss-Hauptquartiers an Ihr Schiff geschickt.",
	["This will be one of the largest {orders} I've ever received during my life. I'll be able to start working on this project right away."] = "To bedzie jedno z najwiekszych {zamowien} jakie w zyciu przyjalem. Bede w stanie zaczac prace nad tym projektem chocby zaraz.",
	["Start by gathering the materials needed to build the spaceship: 20 Gear Wheels, 3 Huge Chunks of Crude Iron, 1 {Glooth Converter}, 3 Gold Ingots, 1 Spark Sphere, 50 Wood, 5 Gearwheel Chains."] = "Zacznij od zebrania materialow potrzebnych do budowy statku: 20 Gear Wheel, 3 Huge Chunk of Crude Iron, 1 {Glooth Converter}, 3 Gold Ingot, 1 Spark Sphere, 50 Wood, 5 Gearwheel Chain",
	["Finding such a device won't be easy. It's possible it will be where Glooth creatures are created. Try your luck in the underground swamps."] = "Takie ustrojstwo nie jest latwo znalezc. Mozliwe, ze bedzie tam, gdzie tworzone sa bestie Glooth. Sproboj szczescia w podziemnych bagnach. ",
	["Good job. I'm getting ready to work on the spaceship. In the meantime, I suggest you start looking for star maps. You'll need them for navigation in space. You'll probably find some map pieces in the city of Bydgoschch, Maioorka. I heard rumors about some witches hiding their map in the ruined chapel, south of maioorka. I think three pieces should be enough for starters. You should also find rocket engine plans. They fell into the hands of the mysterious magician, who allied with outlaws on the north east from Maioor'ka. Now he refuses to share this piece crucial piece. You'll need to acquire both the maps and the engine blueprint for me so I can properly install the rocket propulsion in your vehicle."] = "Dobra robota. Juz sie zbieram do pracy nad statkiem. Tymczasem proponuje, abys zaczal szukac map nieba. Przyda Ci sie, gdy bedziesz nawigowac w kosmosie. Niektore kawalki mapy z pewnoscia znajdziesz w Bydgoshchy i Maioor'ce. Slyszalem pogloski o tym, ze wiedzmy ukryly swoj kawalek w zniszczonej juz kaplicy na poludnie od Maioor'ki. Mysle, ze na poczatek wystarcza Ci trzy kawalki. Jesli chodzi o plany rakietowe: wpadly w rece monopolisty, tj. tajemniczego naukowca, ktory teraz zbratal sie z rozbojnikami. Ich oboz znajdziesz na polnocny wschod od Maioor'ki. Musisz je dla mnie zdobyc, abym mogl poprawnie zainstalowac naped rakietowy w pojezdzie.",
	["As I said, I need: 20 Gear Wheels, 3 Huge Chunks of Crude Iron, 1 {Glooth Converter}, 3 Gold Ingots, 1 Spark Sphere, 50 Wood, 5 Gearwheel Chains."] = "Tak jak mowilem, potrzebuje: 20 Gear Wheel, 3 Huge Chunk of Crude Iron, 1 {Glooth Converter}, 3 Gold Ingot, 1 Spark Sphere, 50 Wood, 5 Gearwheel Chain.",
	["Alright, that's everything I needed. I'll send your spaceship into orbit with a special catapult shortly. I'd have you sit inside it right now, but it's too dangerous. You'll be able to access it through the unlicensed teleporter in the deepling base. Besides, I found this item in my warehouse. If I remember correctly, it's one of the components of rocket fuel. You can produce the fuel by using an atomic splitter on the fuel rod. I've placed this device on your spaceship. You'll also find a remote depot there. I think it will come in handy."] = "Okej, te wszystko czego potrzebowalem. Zaraz wysle twoj statek na orbite specjalna katapula. Dalbym Ci juz teraz usiasc w srodku, ale to zbyt niebezpieczne. Bedziesz mogl sie do niego dostac przez nielicencjonowany teleporter w bazie deeplingow. Oprocz tego znalazlem w moim magazynie ten przedmiot. Jezeli dobrze pamietam, to jest jednym ze skladnikow paliwa rakietowego. Paliwo to mozna wytworzyc poprzez uzycie rozszczepiacza atomow na precie paliwowym. Umiescilem to urzadzenie na twoim statu. Znajdziesz tam rowniez zdalny depozyt. Mysle, ze sie przyda.",
	["I'll need engine blueprints. Also, you'll need to have some basic knowledge of astronomy, so have three sky map pieces with you. Without them, you won't get far."] = "Bede potrzebowac planow silnika. Oprocz tego musisz miec minimalny oglad w astronomii, wiec miej przy sobie trzy kawalki mapy nieba. Bez nich ani rusz.",
	["Flights within a given system require only the power of mana. For intergalactic travel, you'll need rocket fuel. Therefore, you'll need to find a refueling station that sells such fuel. I've included the coordinates of a CPN-sponsored one in the ship's navigation. Good luck!"] = "Loty w obrebie danego ukladu wymagaja wykorzystania jedynie sily przyjazni (many). Do podrozy miedzygalaktycznych potrzebne jest paliwo rakietowe. W zwiazku z tym bedziesz musial znalezc stacje zaopatrzeniowa na ktorej sprzedaja takie paliwa. W nawigacji statku zamiescilem koordynaty sponsorowanego CPN-u. Powodzenia!",
	["Boss, can you spare something to eat? Maybe I could have some {spam} from your inbox?"] = "Kierowniku, poratuj czyms na zab. Moze moglbym zjesc chociaz {spam} z twojej skrzynki?",
	["Thanks, I feel better now. I see you managed to escape from the leather traders' prison. If you want to help me get out of here, I suggest you go to the coachman's room and find something that might be useful to me."] = "Dzieki, juz mi lepiej. Widze, udalo Ci sie uciec z wiezienia handlarzy skor. Jezeli chcesz pomoc mi sie stad wydostac, to proponuje, abys udal sie do pokoju woznego i znalazl cos, co moze mi sie przydac.",
	["Go to the coachman's room now. There are probably various keys and uniforms stored there. It's on the upper floors of this building."] = "Idz teraz do pokoju woznego. Z pewnoscia trzymaja tam rozne klucze i mundury. Znajduje sie na wyzszych pietrach tego budynku.",
	["So, one of the soldiers left their ID document in the dressing room... Maybe you can use that information to convince the main {guard} to release me."] = "A wiec ktorys z zolnierzy zostawil dokument tozsamosci w garderobie... Moze bedziesz mogl wykorzystac te informacje do przekonania glownego {straznika} do wypuszczenia mnie.",
	["Head to the second building on this planet. The main guard, Klaus Schwab, likes to get some fresh air at the top of the tower. Try to negotiate my release with him. Oh, and watch out for the other guards. They won't be as understanding if they see someone in civilian clothes. Also you should only talk to Knopf in his own language, otherwise he will see though charade."] = "Udaj sie do drugiego budynku na tej planecie. Glowny straznik Klaus Schwab lubi zaczerpnac swiezego powietrza na szczycie wiezy. Sproboj z nim wynegocjowac moja wolnosc. Aha, uwazaj na innych straznikow. Oni nie beda tak wyrozumiali, jesli zobacza kogos w cywilu. Aha, jeszcze jedno: musisz rozmawiac z Knopfem w jego wlasnym jezyku, inaczej cie rozpozna.",
	["Do you need fuel? Of course - I sell ready-to-use rocket fuel. The current {exchange rate} is 50,000 crystal coins for 100 liters."] = "Potrzebujesz paliwa? Oczywiscie - sprzedaje gotowe paliwo rakietowe. Aktualny {przelicznik} to 50000 crystal coin za 100 litrow.",
	["If my fuel prices don't suit you, I can sell you a {raw} fuel rod instead."] = "Jezeli nie odpowiadaja Ci moje ceny paliwa, moge Ci sprzedac {surowy} pret paliwowy.",
	["Wait a moment, these rods were stolen from me recently by some clever thieves. I think they were flying towards Ganymede moon. That place is known for its numerous mountain peaks. Most of the mountains and rocks are too dangerous and steep to hide in. The bandits hide in the valleys of the Vaux Maich mountains. I've sent the moon's location to your ship."] = "Chwileczke, te prety zostaly mi ostatnio skradzione przez jakichs cwaniaczkow. Wydaje mi sie, ze odlatywali w strone ksiezyca Jowisza. To miejsce jest znane ze swoich licznych szczytow gorskich. Wiekszosc gor i skal jest jednak zbyt niebezpieczna i stroma, zeby moc sie tam zaszyc. Bandyci chowaja sie w dolinach gor Vaux Maich. Wyslalem informacje o polozeniu ksiezyca do twojego statku.",
	["I don't know what kind of gigachads those thieves must have been to move a crate of that weight."] = "Nie wiem jakimi gigakoksami musieli byc Ci zlodzieje, zeby moc przeniesc pudla o takiej wadze.",
	["Thanks for your help. In return, I can give you one rod. Be careful; they're very heavy! I can sell you more rods for a small fee of 1000 gp each. One more thing: recently, Sad Gentlemen turned up at my station. From an overheard conversation, I learned that they're involved in transporting REDACTED to Hugo Boss's summer cottage."] = "Dzieki za pomoc. W zamian za pomoc moge dac Ci jeden pret. Uwaga, sa bardzo ciezkie! Nastepne prety moge Ci sprzedac za mala oplata w wysokosci 1000 gp. Jeszcze jedna rzecz: ostatnio tankowali u mnie Smutni Panowie. Z podsluchanej rozmowy uslyszalem, ze zajmuja sie transportem ZREDAGOWANO do domku letniskowego hugo bossa.",
	["I know nothing about it."] = "Nic mi o tym nie wiadomo.",
	["Thanks for helping me get out. Keep this - it's my cigarette case that I got for my eighteenth birthday. Personally I don't smoke , so maybe you'll find a better use for it."] = "Dzieki za pomoc w wydostaniu sie. Trzymaj - to moja papierosnica, ktora dostalem na moje osiemnaste urodziny. Ja sam nie pale, wiec moze znajdziesz dla niej lepszy uzytek.",
	["How many rods would you like to buy?"] = "Ile pretow paliwowych chcesz kupic?",
	["Here you go, these are your rods."] = "Prosze, oto twoje prety.",
	["Rocket engine blueprint. Qasim might have a use for it"] = "Plany silnika rakietowego. Qasim moze znac zastosowanie dla niego",
	["Galactic map fragment. Qasim requested three of those"] = "Kawalek mapy nieba. Qasim wspominal, ze bedzie potrzebowac trzech takich fragmentow",
	["Fissile fuel rod"] = "Pret paliwowy",
	["Rocket fuel"] = "Paliwo rakietowe",
	["Crate of rods. Recipient: Swagger"] = "Pudlo z pretami. Zaadresowane do: Swagier",
	["Name: Friedrich Knopf \nNationality: Kuuyvdoobie"] = "Imie: Friedrich Knopf \nNarodowosc: Kujwdubie",
	["Booty Sweat Lean recipe"] = "Przepis na Soczek z Foczek",
	["Scribbles in German. Unreadable"] = "Bazgroly po niemiecku. Nie do odczytania",
	["P0W3R H4MM3R MK3. Collectible - not for professional use"] = "Nie ma chuja na mlotki bogunia! Produkt kolekcjonerski",
	["RubelsteinScrollDesc"] = function(context)
		local player = context.player
		local result = "Bon wdziecznosci na kwote 100000. Do zrealizowania u dowodczyni nomadow. Suma kontrolna: "
		local controlSum = player:getStorageValue(Storage.PerIustitiaAdAstra.RubelsteinChecksum)
		result = result .. tostring(tostring(controlSum))
		return result
	end,
	["I can pay you any amount admitted in a token, effectively charging the party that signed it."] = "Moge ci wyplacic dowwolna kwote, zadluzajac w ten sposob wydajacego czek. Wystarczy, ze podasz sume kontrolna.",
	["Here, take your money."] = "Prosze, oto twoja wyplata.",
	["ShipOk"] = "Ok",
